-- Dow Corning earnings rise
-- 
-- Tue May 1, 2007 8:57am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/05/01/us-dowcorning-results-idUSWEN738920070501

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - Dow Corning Corp. said on Tuesday its first-quarter net income rose 33 percent on the back of strong sales at its semiconductor joint venture and its silicones business. 

 Net income in the quarter rose to $183.6 million from $138 million a year before, while sales climbed 15 percent to $1.18 billion from $1.03 billion. Dow Corning is equally owned by Dow Chemical Co. ( DOW.N ) and Corning Inc. ( GLW.N ).